title: Jelena Dokic's brutally honest revelations on everything from out-of-control eating to online trolls and her abusive father, Damir
description: While she was a top tennis player Dokic said she was riddled with anxiety while dealing with a domineering father and the haunting memories of escaping her homeland as a child.

title: People who sit at work are at greater risk of dying from cardiovascular disease by more than a third compared to workers who stand during their jobs, scientists warn
description: People who mainly sit at work can increase their risk of dying from cardiovascular disease by more than a third, scientists have warned.

title: Hamas October 7 attack has led to 'radicalisation moment' which is influencing young children, with the UK facing the most 'acute threat' of hostile foreign interference and spying since the Cold War, Met Chief warns
description: Matt Jukes, a Metropolitan Police assistant commissioner, likened the convergence of threats to looking at a dashboard of risk indicators where the 'needles are all moving in the wrong direction'.

title: Forecasters reveal when historic freeze that's brought subzero weather to all 48 lower states will finally begin to thaw... but warn that milder weather could be short-lived
description: Forecasters predict that the intense cold gripping much of the country over the past week will take a break but warn that another chilly blast will arrive soon.

title: From teabags to sausages - how we are paying more money for products that are getting smaller and include fewer expensive ingredients
description: Shoppers are getting even less for their money as manufacturers embark on shrinking products and skimping on ingredients including boxes of teabags to sausages.

title: Monster who strangled his girlfriend as she cradled their baby and banned her from breastfeeding is jailed - as his tortured ex bravely speaks out about her years of hell
description: Serial abuser Jonathan Cole, 42, made his pregnant girlfriend Alexis Flavlin's life hell by ripping up their scan picture, forcing her to give birth alone and not allowing her to join baby groups.

title: Former Crossroads actress Charmian Abrahams, 96, is runover and killed by delivery van in Birmingham
description: Ms Abrahams, who starred as Mavis Hooper in the popular British soap during the 1980s, died aged 96 following the fatal collision in Harborne, south-west Birmingham, just before midday on Monday.

title: DAILY MAIL COMMENT: Ignorance on jabs is harming our children
description: DAILY MAIL COMMENT: Measles is not just some childhood rite of passage. It is a highly contagious disease and can be dangerous.

title: Tory ministers will rebuff Labour-led attempt by House of Lords to thwart new Rwanda treaty after Rishi Sunak warned peers not to defy the 'will of the people'
description: The Prime Minister has already warned peers not to defy the 'will of the people' when it starts work on the Safety of Rwanda Bill, which cleared the Commons this week.

title: ABC slammed for social media posts urging people to turn up to 'invasion day' rallies on January 26
description: The ABC is under fire for urging people to attend 'Invasion Day' rallies on January 26 rather than celebrating Australia Day.

title: William Tyrrell's birth mother reveals she is pregnant again - and that's not her only reason to celebrate
description: William Tyrrell 's biological mother is pregnant with her sixth child and has also hinted on one of her social media pages that she may be getting married.

title: Measles can be fatal - trust the science and get your child jabbed says GP and Professor Kamila Hawthorne
description: It's deeply worrying that the rate of uptake for all routine childhood vaccinations is falling - meaning that measles, which can be a serious disease, is on the rise.

title: Health chiefs call for urgent vaccination drive for measles after 'national incident' declared in the UK with warnings that too few youngsters are protected against potentially deadly virus
description: Declaring an official 'national incident', the UK Health Security Agency warned that too few youngsters were protected against measles.

title: Taylor Swift fans fume over glaring error on VIP tickets for the Australian leg of her Eras tour
description: With just a month to go before Taylor Swift brings her highly anticipated concert Down Under, fans who purchased VIP tickets have started to receive their packages - and many are not happy.

title: Former Israeli army chief breaks ranks by declaring a ceasefire is the only hope of seeing hostages released
description: Former army chief Gadi Eisenkot cast doubt on the strategy of battering Gaza into submission and trying to eliminate its terror group rulers.

title: After spending years in African prisons, Old Etonian and ex-SAS mercenary Simon Mann has something to get off his chest: 'I launched the Wonga Coup after Mrs Thatcher told me to just get on with it'
description: It was Lady Thatcher's terse poolside message, Mann says, that cemented his belief that his mission had high-level approval. Had she advised him against it, he might have aborted the venture.

title: Retailers say Gen Z teen shoppers who prefer seeing and touching clothes and who crave real-life social interactions can SAVE America's zombie malls
description: Retail experts say it's the immediacy of touching and trying out products that is driving teenage shoppers back to physical stores, including many struggling shops after the pandemic.

title: CBS Sports host Katie Mox discovers all of her UNDERWEAR and bras have been stolen from her suitcase after catching Delta flight
description: Host Katie Mox of CBS Sports said all of her underwear and bras were stolen from her bag after being checked at an airport on a Delta Air Lines flight. Mox told of her shock on social media.

title: Toronto council BANS tobogganing on 45 hills with furious residents saying 'the fear of liability is ruining modern childhood'
description: Toronto City Council's decision to ban tobogganing on 45 hills in the local area over safety fears has left residents furious.

title: Only dictators ban the free press - yet Nikki Haley gags DailyMail.com simply for reporting a story she doesn't like. So DAVID MARCUS demands: Is she running to be president of America... or a tinpot communist state?
description: MARCUS: Haley holds herself up as the adult in the room - but from this journalist's perspective, she appears to be nothing more than a petty, thin-skinned, petulant child. Perhaps, worse.

title: Now families of teen hostages use haunting Mail page in plea to Washington as US politicians say they'll fight 'like warriors' for Israelis
description: The parents of the teenage girls still held in Gaza travelled to The Capitol in Washington DC where they gave politicians framed copies of the story.

title: $14M engine of US Air Force F-35 is destroyed after maintenance engineer left FLASHLIGHT inside it before test run
description: A $14 million F-35 get engine was written off after a mechanic left a flashlight in the engine following repairs, and then switched the engine on. The engine appeared to be working normally, but then clanged.

title: Apple sparks outrage by introducing transaction fees that could charge iPhone and iPad app users more money
description: The tech giant was ordered by a US judge to change the rules around its so-called 'Apple tax' - a 30 per cent levy on subscriptions and in-app purchases.

title: Fani Willis' 'lover' spent more than $1,000 on FLIGHTS to Miami and San Francisco for the embattled Fulton County DA while he was investigating Trump and they were having an 'improper relationship,' new records show
description: Fani Willis' alleged lover, Special Prosecutor Nathan Wade, spent more than $1,000 on airline tickets so he and the Fulton County District Attorney could travel together.
